The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) acquisition in massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of covariance matrices and pilot sequences also suggests a possible connection to statistical inference (cs.ST) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the focus on spatial correlation in the channel could also make the paper relevant to signal processing (cs.SP).
